Description: Fix multiple segmentation faults and memory safety issues
 This patch addresses several stability issues across the engine:
  * src/livin.c: Added missing 'prev_time = time' update in Cube() to fix
    timing logic. Previously, matat.dv was read at 60fps instead of 30fps,
    leading to excessive file rewinds.
  * src/depthvideo.c: Fixed an off-by-one error where one byte was written
    outside the buffer, and improved EOF (End Of File) validation.
  * src/tridlist.c: Fixed a 'use-after-free' bug in deleteAll() where the 
    'next' pointer was accessed after the current iterator had been freed.
  * src/outline.c: Added a guard in earClipping() to prevent a NULL pointer
    dereference when the vertex count is less than 3.
  * src/face.c & src/bigcube.c: Added mandatory NULL checks for glMapBuffer()
    return values to prevent crashes during buffer mapping failures. 
